oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Men looking at shelving rock
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two men standing underneath Shelter Rock [Shelving Rock]. A plaque is attached to the rock. The man in hat and suspenders reachs one arm towards the plaque, appearing to examine it, with his other hand on his hip.
Where Revolutionary War soldiers camped on their way to King's Mountain.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
